tical and socio-economic context of the time in shaping these women's narcissistic behavior. The study thus inspires a more positive (re-)reading of the protagonists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMotherhood in literature. 0aNarcissism in literature. 4aBritish Studies. 4aGender Studies. 4aGeneral Literature Studies. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aModernism. 4aMotherhood. 4aPsychoanalysis. 4aSelf-Love. 4aTwentieth Century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aBritish Studies.  aGender Studies.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aModernism.  aMotherhood.  aPsychoanalysis.  aSelf-Love.  aTwentieth Century.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2019z978311066277140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839449660zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839449660423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839449660/original  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066277-1  transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-